nserving%20mangroves%20as%20head%20of%20the%20Jharkhali%20Sabuj%20Bahini%2C%20Picture%20source%3A%20Akul%20Biswas%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20impossible%20to%20speak%20of%20mangrove%20cultivation%20and%20protection%20in%20West%20Bengal%20without%20mentioning%20the%20Jharkhali%20Sabuj%20Bahini%20(JSB).%20Comprising%20200%20women%20led%20by%20Akul%20Biswas%2C%20the%20group%20is%20providing%20the%20region%20with%20a%20glimmer%20of%20hope%20in%20the%20face%20of%20the%20rising%20number%20of%20cyclones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Ranjan%20Mondol%2C%20a%20former%20%3Cem%3Egram%20pradhan%3C%2Fem%3E%20(head)%2C%20the%20group%20has%20planted%20around%205%2C00%2C000%20mangrove%20saplings%20covering%20100%20hectares%20in%20Jharkhali%20village%20of%20the%20delta.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMangroves%20in%20India%20are%20distributed%20across%20nine%20states%20and%20three%20union%20territories%20with%20West%20Bengal%20having%20the%20highest%20mangrove%20cover%20of%202%2C114%20sq%20km.%20Observing%20how%20places%20with%20less%20vegetation%20were%20easily%20inundated%2C%20Biswas%20saw%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F352436%2Fmangrove-plantation-sundarbans-afforestation-conservation-south-parganas-west-bengal-cyclone-blind-activist%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emangroves%20as%20the%20only%20hope%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20region.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shrubs%20act%20as%20a%20natural%20barrier%20against%20flooding%20and%20waves%20during%20cyclones%2C%20he%20notes.%20In%202005%2C%20he%20started%20to%20plant%20mangroves%20along%20the%20banks%20of%20the%20Bidyadhari%20River%20and%20was%20soon%20joined%20by%20the%20local%20women.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20confident%20of%20their%20approach%2C%20it%20was%20in%20May%202021%20that%20they%20saw%20the%20impact%20of%20their%20efforts%20when%20Cyclone%20Yaas%20hit%20the%20area.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20%5Bthe%2