amp%3B%20Distributed%202%20Lakh%20Saplings%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKokum%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20a%20rare%20and%20cherished%20sour-tasting%20fruit%2C%20frequently%20features%20in%20the%20cuisine%20of%20people%20living%20in%20the%20Western%20Ghats%20region%20of%20India.%20Despite%20its%20popularity%2C%20this%20savoury%20fruit%20is%20becoming%20increasingly%20scarce%20due%20to%20the%20decline%20in%20its%20plantations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMost%20of%20it%20only%20grew%20wild%20without%20any%20proper%20care%20or%20irrigation.%20They%20were%20almost%20going%20extinct%20when%20my%20father%20started%20to%20grow%20them%20on%20our%20plantation%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Ramesh%20Rai%20(68)%2C%20the%20son%20of%20Narayana%20Rai%20%E2%80%94%20a%20farmer%20from%20Ballikan%20village%20in%20Puttur%2C%20who%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20people%20who%20realised%20the%20decline%20in%20the%20production%20of%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Eand%20started%20planting%20the%20fruit.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKnown%20scientifically%20as%20Garcinia%20indica%2C%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20a%20fruit-bearing%20plant%20in%20the%20mangosteen%20family.%20It%20is%20commonly%20found%20in%20the%20Western%20Ghats%20region%20of%20India.%20Devoured%20for%20its%20savoury%20taste%2C%20it%20is%20also%20known%20as%20%3Cem%3Ebheranda%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20Marathi%2C%20%3Cem%3Ekudampuli%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20Malayalam%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Ekodampuli%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20Tamil.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20Narayana%20passed%20away%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20his%20family%2C%20especially%20his%20son%2C%20has%20been%20carrying%20forward%20his%20legacy.%20Narayana%E2%80%99s%20estate%2C%20now%20managed%20by%20his%20son%2C%20boasts%20over%2010%2C000%20blooming%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Etrees%20that%20are%20actively%20producing%20fruit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Better%20India%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20sat%20down%20with%20Ramesh%20to%20understand%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20vision%20and%20what%20Ramesh%20is%20doing%20to%20take%20it%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EA%20leap%20of%20faith%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamesh%20fondly%20recalls%20when%20his%20father%20predicted%20that%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewould%20be%20in%20high%20demand%20in%20the%20future.%20Talking%20about%20the%20history%20of%20the%20estate%20and%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20dream%2C%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20father%20acquired%20our%20property%20in%201950%2C%20transforming%20what%20was%20then%20a%20dense%20forest%20into%20a%20plantation.%20Initially%2C%20we%20planted%20areca%2C%20rubber%2C%20coconut%2C%20jackfruit%2C%20and%20cashew.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20Ramesh%E2%80%99s%20father%20was%20farming%20different%20plants%2C%20it%20was%20about%2015%20years%20ago%20that%20he%20began%20planting%20Kokum%2C%20anticipating%20its%20future%20demand%20due%20to%20its%20medicinal%20value.%20%E2%80%9CHe%20started%20growing%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Ebecause%20of%20his%20love%20for%20the%20fruit!%20Furthermore%2C%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Eplants%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20much%20water%20and%20grow%20well%20in%20the%20local%20climate%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20shares%20that%20his%20father%20planted%20around%2012%2C000%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Eplants%2C%20of%20which%20approximately%2010%2C000%20have%20survived.%20%3Cem%3EKokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20highly%20sought%20after%20in%20North%20India%20for%20its%20use%20in%20making%20oils%20and%20beverages.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20confident%20that%20the%20price%20of%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewould%20rise%2C%20and%20we%20decided%20to%20wait%20for%20the%20plants%20to%20mature.%20Initially%2C%20the%20price%20was%20around%20Rs%2010%20per%20kg%2C%20but%20it%20has%20now%20risen%20to%20Rs%20120%20to%20130%20per%20kg%2C%20and%20in%20some%20places%2C%20it%20can%20go%20up%20to%20Rs%20300%20per%20kg%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20840px)%20100vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Narayan%20Rai%2C%20Ramesh's%20father.%20%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537.jpg%20840w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537-500x261.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537-768x401.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F07%2Ffeature-photos-44-1-1721390537-150x78.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-357728%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22439%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ENarayan%20Rai%2C%20Ramesh%E2%80%99s%20father.%20%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Narayan%20started%20farming%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eeveryone%20thought%20that%20it%20was%20a%20waste%20of%20time.%20However%2C%20for%20him%2C%20this%20meant%20the%20loss%20of%20a%20native%20tree%2C%20which%20he%20did%20not%20want.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamesh%20adds%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20initial%20challenges%20my%20father%20faced%20were%20significant.%20Farmers%20found%20it%20hard%20to%20believe%20that%20a%20simple%20plant%20like%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Ecould%20solve%20their%20problems.%20Since%20%3Cem%3Ekokum%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20not%20well-known%20and%20had%20little%20demand%20in%20the%20market%2C%20farmers%20were%20reluctant%20to%20waste%20their%20time%20growing%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ESaving%20the%20native%20plant%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERamesh%20recalls%20that%20his%20father%20Narayan%20took%20it%20upon